My thoughts on what has been happening in the United States today. There are tears in my eyes as I think of the destruction of so many lives. The families of those who were innocent victims of this tragedy. Those in public service and safety who will be working 24/7 to search thru the rubble for survivors. Those who are in the military who have always known of the possibilty of war that may now become a reality. <br>
<br>
Alan gave me a call as I was trying to write this. He said he was busy working and would probably not be home tonight. My concern turns to those who are not as fortunate. Who face the uncertainty, not knowing where their loved ones are or if they will return. <br>
<br>
To my friends, to those MW's who are also in the military, and those who are suffering, my thoughts and prayers are with you. <br>
<br>
Love,<br>
