<br>
I had the day off today, so I slept in. Only to be awaken by my sister-in-law's frantic message on my answering machine. I called her back and she told me to turn on the TV. My heart stopped when I heard what had happened. <br>
<br>
My eyes filled in tears thinking of all the people that have died in this senseless act. War is here. And it saddens me. I never thought that I would see an all out war in my lifetime. <br>
<br>
I mourn all that have been lost. My hearts and prayers go out to all the families that have lost loved ones, to all the families and military personnel that will be affected. <br>
<br>
I urge you all to take a moment of silence, no matter what your religious affiliation is, in honor of all that have been lost and all those that will fight for our country in this tragic time.<br>
<br>
As Always<br>
<br>
